{"author":{"id":"179e9b0ea582e3758e82bf8194a7d2f898c41bf99cc80245f0d5c83eeb6363cd"},"ops":[{"type":6,"timestamp":1560826554,"nonce":"d5x8J0qWDwRHSZSHZq84RU9+VII=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdDIzNzQwNTY2MA=="},"target":"eac4fea7d75e07b71907548786ffd3890190a10a4861395af1e9971e1a88f1a3","message":"It seems that the picard RNA-seq metrics wrapper accepts both GFF/GTF and [refflat](https://genome.ucsc.edu/goldenpath/gbdDescriptionsOld.html#RefFlat)\n\nThere are instructions for extracting  UCSC gene info at the bottom of the tool, but this does not generate actual refflat, \n\nrefflat format:\n```\nDDX11L1 ENST00000456328.2       chr1    +       11868   14409   14409   14409   3       11868,12612,13220,      12227,12721,14409,\n```\nucsc extract format:\n```\nENST00000456328.2       chr1    +       11868   14409   14409   14409   3       11868,12612,13220,      12227,12721,14409, DDX11L1\n```\n\n2 options:\n- add a ucsc extract format (and simplify instructions to allow extracting \"all fields from the selected table\")\n- sniff which refflat we have using data in column 4 (numeric = ucsc extract, +/- = refflat)\n\nWhich should I implement?\nOr a third option I've not considered?\nsee also #1254","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1560831667,"nonce":"wQcXbnQszBdZyWIHM6Ji3gm21bE=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDUwMjk0MDE5OA==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/2453#issuecomment-502940198"},"message":"the sniff was simple... so I went that route.","files":null}]}